Package com.example.ceandroid

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DeleteDialogFragment.DeleteDialogListener
    Delete Dialog Listener Interface
    DeleteDialogFragmentRule.DeleteDialogListenerRule
    DeleteDialogListenerRule Interface
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    About
    About page - accessed via Preferences
    ActionExecuter
    The Action Executor Class executes Effects
    CategoryList
    Category List Fragment This class is used to organize Rules/Causes/Effects by Category Currently not being used
    CauseView
    CauseView Class displays the list of Causes
    CEapp
    CEapp stores all globally accessible information for the application
    CEbr
    CEbr is the BroadcastReceiver that is run on the CEservice to handle OS triggers This class is the start of the entire Rules Engine flow
    CEservice
    Service to handle device state changes and evaluate rules accordingly
    DatabaseHandler
    Database class used for everything Database-related
    DeleteDialogFragment
    Delete Dialog displayed when an item is to be deleted from a List
    DeleteDialogFragmentRule
    Creates the DialogFragment for deleting rules from the MyRules Activity
    EditRule
    The EditRule class is the main Activity for rule creation This Activity is used for creating, editing, and viewing rules The Rule creation constantly comes back to this screen to show the user the progress on the rule creation The rCauses, rCause boolean logic, rEffects, Rule Name, and Rule Active Status are all displayed on this Activity
    EditRuleNode
    Custom object used for AND/OR list manipulation in EditRule
    EffectView
    EffectView Class displays the list of Effects
    ExpressionTree
    Uses the tree string stored in a rule to build a tree, fills leaf nodes with rCause objects, and evaluates/returns a result
    ExpressionTree.TreeNode
    Nodes for tree building.
    FileUtils
    FileUtils handles the File Utility Byte for byte copies
    General
    "General settings" page
    Help
    This Help Class provides an image link to our private tutorial on Wordpress
    MainActivity  
    MyRules
    MyRules Class displays the list of Rules
    Preferences
    Preferences page - tabbed interface to get access to other pages
    Rule
    The Rule classic is the underlying data structure for the entire program Causes and Effects, as well as other rule information, is stored within this object
    RulesEngine
    Used for rule evaluation.
    Security
    Page for showing security options
    ShareList
    Page for displaying available rules to share.
    ShareNFC
    Page to push rules to another device via NFC
    TabListener<T extends Fragment>
    TabListener taken from sample code at developer.android.com
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ActionExecuter.Type
    Currently Stored Effect Types This can be removed if the switch statement above uses strings instead
    CauseView.cEnum
    List of Causes currently being used in the application This can be removed if strings are used for the switch statement
    EffectView.eEnum
    List of effects currently being used in the application This can be removed if strings are used for the switch statement
